* Notes:\n \nI2C communication, analog MUX (AMUX), Watchdog timer, die temperature\nmonitoring, factory ship mode, and top-off state are not modeled.\nFor GPIO, only the input function is modeled.\nFor the nEN pin, the model assumes push-button input. \n \nThe following parameters model the corresponding register settings.\nUse decimal numbers for the settings, e.g., use 17 for 0x11. \n \n1. TV0, TV1, TV2, TVLDO: target voltages for SBB0/1/2 and LDO.\n2. IP0, IP1, IP2, IP3: peak currents of SBB0/1/2 and charging channel. \n3. EN0, EN1, EN2, EN_LDO: chanel enable for SBB0/1/2 and LDO. \n4. MD0, MD1, MD2, MD3: operation mode of SBB0/1/2 and charging channel.\n5. ADE0,  ADE1, ADE2, ADE_LDO: active discharge enable for SBB0/1/2 and LDO.\n6. CHG_EN: charger enable\n7. THM_EN: thermistor enable\n8. VCHG: fast-charge voltage\n9. VCHG_J: JEITA-modified fast-charge voltage\n10. ICHG: fast-charge current\n11. ICHG_J: JEITA-modified fast-charge current\n12. LDO_MD: LDO operation mode\n13. GPI_RF: GPI edge detection. 0, 1, 2 stand for falling, rising, and\nboth edges, respectively. A valid edge triggers a 10us active low\npulse on the nIRQ pin.\n \nThe following parameters can be customized to reduce simulation time.\nThey may not be programmable on the real part.\n \n1. tDB_i: nEN pin debounce time.\n2. tChDB_i: CHGIN pin debounce time. \n3. tGIDB_i: GPI pin debounce time.\n4. tRST_i: manual reset duration\n5. tOFF_i: WAIT time for off actions \n6. tPQ_i: pre-qualification timer
